1
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:18,890
You call this clean?

2
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,880
I think it's fine.

3
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:24,480
Back when I roamed the world,

4
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:26,410
I stayed in worse places than this.

5
00:01:27,160 --> 00:01:29,880
The Young Marquis is used to luxury.

6
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:31,400
He can't handle hardship.

7
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:33,259
Who says I can't handle hardship?

8
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:35,400
Innkeeper! We need rooms.

9
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,920
Coming, coming.

10
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:48,120
Guests this late?

11
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:51,680
Looks like a good haul today.

12
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:57,360
Innkeeper, do you have many guests today?

13
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:00,440
In the middle of the night,

14
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:02,680
apart from you,

15
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:06,760
who else would be here?

16
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,100
Money isn't a problem.

17
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,000
Give us three of your best rooms.

18
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,400
Make sure they're clean.

19
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,760
This way upstairs, please.

20
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:18,720
The rooms

21
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:21,320
are guaranteed clean.

22
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:57,840
This horse is acting weird.

23
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:01,080
It just stopped moving for no reason.

24
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:04,120
And this is the only shabby inn around.

25
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:07,240
We'll have to wait until morning

26
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:09,040
to buy two horses in town.

27
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:14,840
Let's just make do for tonight.

28
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,600
I just hope it doesn't delay tomorrow's business.

29
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,960
Do you want water?

30
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,760
I'm talking to you.

31
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:36,520
What's wrong?

32
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,079
Good heavens!

33
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:53,960
Raising Gu in the living is better than in the dead.

34
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:56,360
Look how well they're growing.

35
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,060
Thanks to your secret technique.

36
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,440
I say,

37
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:05,240
these Gu worms are a goldmine.

38
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:08,440
We used to have to bury the bodies.

39
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:12,720
Now we just count the silver.

40
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,640
It's a good method,

41
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,720
but extremely dangerous.

42
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,400
One slip up,

43
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:29,040
and we become food for these creatures.

44
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:30,560
Remember,

45
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:34,000
this must never be leaked.

46
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:37,360
Or our lives are forfeit.

47
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,360
Don't worry.

48
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,560
I know the risks.

49
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:42,600
But,

50
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:45,520
these babies are full now.

51
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:48,280
What about the fat sheep that came earlier?

52
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,440
Drug him later,

53
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:52,320
tie him up and keep him for now.

54
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,640
Go keep an eye on them.

55
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:57,360
Tell me if anything happens.

56
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,159
Okay.

57
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,400
Leave it to me.

58
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,720
What happened?

59
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,610
The living dead.

60
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:50,200
Where did you learn this witchcraft?

61
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:56,320
I don't know what you're talking about.

62
00:05:57,320 --> 00:06:04,040
Our inn is just a rest stop for travelers.

63
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:08,840
There's no witchcraft here.

64
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,920
Actually,

65
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,560
I want to ask this young lady.

66
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:17,680
Why did my guest

67
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:21,680
become a walking corpse after meeting you?

68
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:26,760
Lord Fang is an Imperial Envoy appointed by the Emperor.

69
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:29,520
He's here to investigate the witchcraft case.

70
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:31,240
Now we have the evidence and the culprit.

71
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,770
If you still dare to deny it,

72
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:36,220
we have the right to execute first and report later.

73
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:53,280
Just like the dancer at Qihong Tower.

74
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,800
I'll talk! I know!

75
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,500
She mentioned before,

76
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:02,640
her Gu worms came from...

77
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,760
from Wangjiapu.

78
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:08,880
This inn is our base for raising Gu.

79
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,000
And...

80
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,960
we make some extra money from these merchants.

81
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:18,040
To get those guests to come into the inn,

82
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:20,240
I went to the small path outside

83
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,720
and scattered some poison powder.

84
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:24,120
Any horse that touches it will feign death.

85
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,480
Tell me.

86
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:29,480
What's this about the ghosts?

87
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:32,220
I don't know anything about that.

88
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,280
I just heard

89
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:38,080
that ghosts have been appearing in Wangjiapu at night recently.

90
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,120
It's terrifying.

91
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:43,680
I just used that rumor to scare the guests

92
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,020
into entering the inn.

93
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,659
It was all for a living.

94
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:49,920
My lord,

95
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:52,800
please spare me.

96
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:54,920
Let me live.

97
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,920
I know I was wrong.

98
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,120
I know I was wrong.

99
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:01,440
Please, give me a way out.

100
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,720
A way out?

101
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:07,080
I'll take you to the Dragon Shadow Guard tomorrow

102
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:08,640
and find a way out for you.

103
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:14,640
With all this talk of ghosts and witchcraft,

104
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:18,280
could it be the same group of people

105
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:20,320
playing tricks?

106
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,160
Tomorrow,

107
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:27,640
let's go to Wangjiapu and take a look.

108
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,840
What's wrong?

109
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:06,360
Why are you in my room?

110
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,840
I have sharp ears and eyes.

111
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,660
I heard you screaming in the middle of the night.

112
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:17,620
If I hadn't come, the noise would have killed me.

113
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:20,560
Yan'er.

114
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:22,960
Yan'er.

115
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:25,200
Yan'er.

116
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,400
Gu Lihan.

117
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:29,400
Yan'er.

118
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,120
Gu Lihan.

119
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:34,560
Are you okay?

120
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:35,560
No.

121
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,120
Don't.

122
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,040
Don't worry.

123
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:40,720
I'm here.

124
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,480
No one will bully you.

125
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:45,960
Really?

126
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:56,480
I was afraid your screaming would disturb others' sleep,

127
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,680
so I sat here and kept watch all night.

128
00:09:59,120 --> 00:09:59,920
Thanks.

129
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:03,480
So,

130
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:08,720
did I say anything in my sleep?

131
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,240
You seemed frightened by those corpses.

132
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:15,800
You kept saying "Run" and "No".

133
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:21,120
I need to take You Ershun back first.

134
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,040
Do you want to come along?

135
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:26,240
I won't join you.

136
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,330
Wangjiapu isn't far from here.

137
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:31,680
I'll go with Official Fang to investigate the case first.

138
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:32,480
All right.

139
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:34,080
Be careful then.

140
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,120
Mm-hmm.

141
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,400
I'll take You Ershun to Jinzhou

142
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:46,400
and wait for you at Changhe Station.

143
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,400
Okay.

144
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:51,800
And...

145
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:54,120
Fang Ji isn't good at martial arts.

146
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,880
Don't force a fight if anything happens.

147
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:57,120
Wait for me to come back and teach them a lesson.

148
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:57,850
Don't worry.

149
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,040
Okay.

150
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:12,560
You're here too.

151
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:31,960
Min Si's wife,

152
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,600
she usually looks so honest and timid.

153
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,400
I didn't expect her to be so bold.

154
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,000
Let me tell you,

155
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:39,010
you never really know a person.

156
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:39,960
Now,

157
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,600
without a man in the house to control her,

158
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,130
she's capable of anything.

159
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:46,440
I know your dirty little minds.

160
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,440
Don't think the authorities won't catch you.

161
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:53,170
The imperial penal code is designed to guard against scum like you.

162
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,640
Lord Xiong is kind and benevolent.

163
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:00,100
You unruly people.

164
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:01,400
You are so brazen,

165
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:04,420
stealing salt from the government granary to sell.

166
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:06,290
Speak up.

167
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:09,040
How should we punish those who steal?

168
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:11,000
Put her in a pig cage!

169
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,600
Drown her in the salt fields!

170
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:12,960
That's right.

171
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:13,800
Beat her to a pulp!

172
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:14,240
Slut!

173
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,520
Beat this slut to death!

174
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:16,960
Good!

175
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:17,970
Beat her!

176
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,080
Cao Agou!

177
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:25,480
You're framing me.

178
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:28,840
You tricked me into going to the salt warehouse to exchange salt,

179
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,520
but you tried to grope me.

180
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:31,850
You had bad intentions.

181
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:33,400
I bit your ear,

182
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:36,200
so you falsely accused me of stealing salt.

183
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,960
You wretched woman, you...

184
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:39,200
You!

185
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:45,960
Stop!

186
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,360
A group of you

187
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:53,240
are bullying a defenseless woman in public.

188
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:55,160
You convicted her in just a few words.

189
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,720
This isn't upholding justice.

190
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,520
This is just venting your anger.

191
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,200
You look unfamiliar.

192
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:02,120
Who are you?

193
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,080
Guards! Seize him!

194
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:04,640
Wait.

195
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:09,090
Where did a wild man like you come from?

196
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,400
I know.

197
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:17,440
You and Min Huishi must have some dirty secret.

198
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:20,840
I met this woman for the first time today.

199
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,280
I was just passing by,

200
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:25,360
and I couldn't stand watching this.

201
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:27,400
Justice in this world

202
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:30,480
cannot be trampled upon by villains at will.

203
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,240
What an arrogant brat who doesn't know his place.

204
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,100
How dare you spout nonsense here!

205
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:38,680
If you really have nothing to do with Min Huishi,

206
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:41,180
then why are you making trouble here?

207
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:44,720
They say gossip follows a widow's door.

208
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,840
This little hussy is good-looking.

209
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,160
After her man died,

210
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,560
she surely couldn't stand the loneliness.

211
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,760
I couldn't tell.

212
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,780
I really met this woman for the first time today.

213
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:58,560
Stop playing dumb.

214
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:01,020
If you haven't met her, why speak for her?

215
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:02,480
Don't you all agree?

216
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,400
That's right!

217
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:03,960
Exactly.

218
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:04,560
Yes.

219
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,120
Who knows?

220
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,080
Before her husband died,

221
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,680
the two of them might have been fooling around.

222
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:21,240
A glance at the misty rain, a fleeting dream.

223
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:28,120
A touch of moonlight sings alone to the breeze.

224
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:32,040
Flowers bloom in the silent night with persistence.

225
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:35,760
The promise made by the youth yesterday.

226
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:37,640
Is for love.
